: Topological sort of plugins based on dependencies\n  - Detects circular dependencies\n  - Detects missing dependencies\n  - Returns ordered plugin array\n- **build()**: Main build process\n  1. Copies files into BuildContext\n  2. Executes all beforeBuild hooks in dependency order\n  3. Applies transformContent hooks to all files in dependency order\n  4. Renders templates using template engine (or outputs raw content if no template)\n  5. Executes all afterBuild hooks in dependency order\n  6. Returns complete BuildContext\n- **getPlugins()** / **getTemplates()**: Accessors that return copies\n\n**Templates (src/core/templates.ts):**\n- **createDefaultTemplate()**: Renders article with title, date, content in HTML wrapper\n- **createListTemplate()**: Renders list-style content in HTML wrapper\n\n### 3. Test Files Summary\n\n#### Core Tests (tests/core.test.ts) - 16 test cases\n\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration\n3. Default template rendering with variables\n4. List template rendering\n5. Raw content output when no template\n6. beforeBuild hook execution\n7. transformContent hook application\n8. afterBuild hook execution\n9. Plugin execution in dependency order\n10. Circular dependency detection\n11. Missing dependency detection\n12. Multiple plugin transformContent in order\n13. Shared data store in context\n14. File metadata retention\n15. Empty output for empty file list\n\n#### Plugin Tests\n\n**search-index.test.ts** (7 tests):\n- Generates search-index.json in output\n- Strips HTML tags from indexed content\n- Includes code blocks in search\n- Handles empty files\n- Valid JSON output\n- Includes tags if present\n\n**rss-feed.test.ts** (7 tests):\n- Valid RSS 2.0 XML generation\n- HTML content in CDATA sections\n- Category tags from taxonomy\n- Channel title from config\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates\n- Link URLs use baseUrl from config\n\n**sitemap.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Generates sitemap.xml\n- Includes all content page URLs\n- Includes taxonomy tag page URLs\n- Includes feed.xml URL\n- URLs use baseUrl from config\n- Valid XML structure\n- Handles sites with no tag pages\n\n**dev-server.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Stores dev-server-config in ctx.data\n- Config includes port setting\n- Includes asset routes from asset-pipeline\n- Includes search index path\n- Includes content routes\n- Default port is 3000\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline gracefully\n\n**asset-pipeline.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path\n- Rewrites relative link URLs to /assets/ path\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged\n- Generates asset manifest in ctx.data\n- Handles files with no asset references\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Doesn't double-process already-rewritten URLs\n\n**taxonomy.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Builds tag index from file tags\n- Generates tag listing pages\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles files with multiple tags\n- Tag pages list all files with that tag\n- Stores tag map in ctx.data\n- Handles empty file list\n- Tags normalized to lowercase\n\n**markdown-ext.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Converts basic markdown to HTML\n- Handles footnotes with [^1] syntax\n- Renders footnote section at bottom\n- Converts :::note container to admonition div\n- Converts :::warning container to admonition div\n- Converts :::tip container to admonition div\n- Preserves existing HTML content\n- Handles empty content\n\n**syntax-highlight.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Adds language class to code blocks\n- Adds data-language attribute to pre tags\n- Handles multiple code blocks\n- Handles code blocks with no language specified\n- Adds highlighted class to processed blocks\n- Preserves code block content\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Does not modify inline code\n\n### 4. Configuration Files\n\n**package.json**:\n- Name: bench-ssg-toolkit v1.0.0\n- Type: module (ES modules)\n- Scripts: build (tsc), lint (eslint), test (vitest run)\n- Dependencies: express, marked, @types/express, @types/marked\n- DevDependencies: TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint\n\n**tsconfig.json**:\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Output to ./dist, source from ./src\n\n**vitest.config.ts**:\n- Global test helpers enabled\n- 10-second test timeout\n\n### Expected Plugin Implementations\n\nBased on the test files, you need to implement these plugins in `src/plugins/`:\n\n1. **search-index.js** - Creates `createSearchIndexPlugin()` with afterBuild hook\n2. **rss-feed.js** - Creates `createRssFeedPlugin()` with afterBuild hook\n3. **sitemap.js** - Creates `createSitemapPlugin()` with afterBuild hook\n4. **dev-server.js** - Creates `createDevServerPlugin()` with afterBuild hook\n5. **asset-pipeline.js** - Creates `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` with transformContent hook\n6. **taxonomy.js** - Creates `createTaxonomyPlugin()` with beforeBuild and afterBuild hooks\n7. **markdown-ext.js** - Creates `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` with transformContent hook\n8. **syntax-highlight.js** - Creates `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` with transformContent hook\n\nAll plugins follow the Plugin interface pattern and are exported as factory functions returning Plugin objects with appropriate hooks."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ace8c2acdb40fed0a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37014\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 28803</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"1bbf32c0-ae85-41ea-91e6-6c4ed4f159ec","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:21:35.138Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full project structure (all files)\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts\n3. The build engine in src/core/\n4. All test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n5. The existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n\nRead ALL files completely - don't skip any. I need the full content of every test file to underst